event.name: Welcome Week
event.short_desc: This event will give an overview of the whole week's plans, as well as introductions to all the 'people-to-know' on campus.
event.main_desc: Welcome Week is designed for you – with lots of exciting activities, campus tours, and social events experienced within a community of students who will make you delighted that you chose TERMINALFOUR University. Make sure you get involved.

event.name: Commencement Ceremony
event.short_desc: A record number of graduates this year plus more than 10,000 friends and family members due to attend.
event.main_desc:
During this ceremony degrees will be conferred for all bachelor's and master's candidates. 

Tickets

Although tickets are not required for Commencement ceremonies, and there is no limit to the number of guests you may bring, there will be limited seating in the smaller venues based on the number of students participating. 

How do I get my cap and gown?
Students will be emailed information and instructions on how to order regalia from the Commencement Office.

Official photographs

The university’s official photographer, will take photographs of each graduate participating in the commencement ceremony prior to the procession and also as students cross the platform.

Congratulations to all graduates this year, enjoy your speical day.

event.name: T4U Campus Visit
event.short_desc: TERMINALFOUR University is opening its doors for a day, and you have a golden ticket.
event.main_desc:
You don’t have to attend an open day to apply to TERMINALFOUR University but visiting us does give you a chance to get a real feel for the University.

During the day there will be lots of presentations that outline what TERMINALFOUR University has to offer it's students. Here you'll get information on the application procedure, on student life and important advice on the available financial support for our students.

Our helpful staff and students will be on hand throughout the day to answer any questions you may have about studying at TERMINALFOUR University.

event.name: Library Opening Ceremony
event.short_desc: TERMINALFOUR University is opening it's brand new, state of the art library.
event.main_desc:
This new library has more than 100 public access computers, theatres, an exhibition gallery and music rooms.

It has been built to replace the previous University Library, built in the 1960s.

Most of the funding has come from our incredibly generous alumni as well as fundraising by student groups over the last number of years. It is a hude asset to the future of TERMINALFOUR University, and it's students.

The hope of all at T4U is that this library will continue to enlighten future generations.
